    <p>{`Before you begin testing we suggest visiting the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/testrunner-toolkit"
      }}>{`Testrunner Toolkit`}</a>{` home page as well as the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/testrunner-toolkit/configuration"
      }}>{`configuration`}</a>{` page.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "what-youll-need"
    }}>{`What You'll Need`}</h2>
    <p>{`Refer to the requirements listed on the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/testrunner-toolkit/installation"
      }}>{`Installation`}</a>{` page.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "create-a-configuration"
    }}>{`Create a Configuration`}</h2>
    <p>{`Creating a configuration is a crucial step before you begin testing. Without the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`config.yml`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`saucectl`}</inlineCode>{` has no idea which framework to use during testing. Please visit the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/testrunner-toolkit/configuration"
      }}>{`Configuration`}</a>{` page for detailed information on how to create or edit a configuration.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "run-your-first-test"
    }}>{`Run Your First Test`}</h2>
    <p>{`Run the following command to execute you first test and to ensure Testrunner works properly:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`saucectl run
`}</code></pre>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-note alert alert--secondary"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "14",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 14 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M6.3 5.69a.942.942 0 0 1-.28-.7c0-.28.09-.52.28-.7.19-.18.42-.28.7-.28.28 0 .52.09.7.28.18.19.28.42.28.7 0 .28-.09.52-.28.7a1 1 0 0 1-.7.3c-.28 0-.52-.11-.7-.3zM8 7.99c-.02-.25-.11-.48-.31-.69-.2-.19-.42-.3-.69-.31H6c-.27.02-.48.13-.69.31-.2.2-.3.44-.31.69h1v3c.02.27.11.5.31.69.2.2.42.31.69.31h1c.27 0 .48-.11.69-.31.2-.19.3-.42.31-.69H8V7.98v.01zM7 2.3c-3.14 0-5.7 2.54-5.7 5.68 0 3.14 2.56 5.7 5.7 5.7s5.7-2.55 5.7-5.7c0-3.15-2.56-5.69-5.7-5.69v.01zM7 .98c3.86 0 7 3.14 7 7s-3.14 7-7 7-7-3.12-7-7 3.14-7 7-7z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`default test location`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`Unless you specify a test directory, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`saucectl`}</inlineCode>{` executes tests based on the framework's default test directory. For example with a cypress test, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`saucectl`}</inlineCode>{` will attempt to locate `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`cypress.json`}</inlineCode>{`, as well as the default `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`cypress`}</inlineCode>{` directory.`}</p><p parentName="div">{`Consult your desired framework's documentation for more information about the default test locations.`}</p></div></div>
    <p><inlineCode parentName="p">{`saucectl`}</inlineCode>{` then kicks off a test run and will:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`pull the necessary docker images/layers (e.g. `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`saucelabs/stt-cypress-mocha-node:v<tag>`}</inlineCode>{`)`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`copy/mount your test files to the docker container`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`run the tests within the docker container`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`display the test results in the console`}</li>
    </ul>
    <p>{`Testrunner Toolkit will then execute the test based on the information in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`config.yml`}</inlineCode>{`. `}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "test-on-sauce-labs"
    }}>{`Test on Sauce Labs`}</h2>
    <p><small>supported frameworks: <Highlight color="#25c2a0" mdxType="Highlight">cypress</Highlight></small></p>
    <p>{`If you wish to run your tests on Sauce Labs VMs, simply run the following command:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`saucectl run --test-env sauce
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`If you wish to increase your VM concurrency you can also use the flag `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--ccy <vm number>`}</inlineCode>{`. `}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`saucectl run --test-env sauce --ccy 2
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`You can also designate `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`concurrency`}</inlineCode>{` in the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`config.yml`}</inlineCode>{` like so:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-yaml",
        "metastring": "{2}",
        "{2}": true
      }}>{`sauce:
  concurrency: 3
  region: us-west-1
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Please note that VM concurrency depends on the suite number rather than the number of `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`.spec.js |.test.js`}</inlineCode>{` files. Plese visit the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/testrunner-toolkit/saucectl#ccy"
      }}>{`CLI Reference`}</a>{` for more information regarding command parameters:`}</p>
    <blockquote>
      <p parentName="blockquote">{`Your concurrency and VM entitlements also depend on your Sauce Labs subscription tier. For more information please visit the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
          "href": "https://saucelabs.com/pricing"
        }}>{`pricing guide`}</a></p>
    </blockquote>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "cross-browser-tests"
    }}>{`Cross-Browser Tests`}</h3>
    <p><small>supported frameworks: <Highlight color="#25c2a0" mdxType="Highlight">cypress</Highlight></small></p>
    <p>{`When you run tests on Sauce Labs VMs you have access to a wide range of OS + browser combinations. In order to test against multiple different browsers, you can indicate the desired combinations in the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`suites`}</inlineCode>{` > `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`browser`}</inlineCode>{` field:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-yaml",
        "metastring": "{4,11,18}",
        "{4,11,18}": true
      }}>{`suites:
  # Chrome
  - name: "Swag Labs Login Chrome"
    browser: "chrome"
    platformName: "Windows 10"
    screenResolution: "1400x1050"
    config:
      testFiles: [ "**/login.*" ]
  # MicrosoftEdge
  - name: "Swag Labs Login MicrosoftEdge"
    browser: "MicrosoftEdge"
    platformName: "Windows 10"
    screenResolution: "1400x1050"
    config:
      testFiles: [ "**/login.*" ]
 # Firefox
   - name: "Swag Labs Login Firefox"
     browser: "firefox"
     platformName: "Windows 10"
     screenResolution: "1400x1050"
     config:
       testFiles: [ "**/login.*" ]
`}</code></pre>
    <blockquote>
      <p parentName="blockquote">{`For full examples, please `}<a parentName="p" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/saucelabs-training/demo-js/tree/master/testrunner-toolkit"
        }}>{`visit this repository`}</a></p>
    </blockquote>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "using-sauce-connect"
    }}>{`Using Sauce Connect`}</h3>
    <p>{`If you're running tests on Sauce Labs VMs, but the site under test is protected behind strict network security/policies, you can utilize `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/secure-connections/sauce-connect"
      }}>{`Sauce Connect Proxy`}</a>{` to circumvent the problem.`}</p>
    <p>{`You can use the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--tunnel-id`}</inlineCode>{` flag with `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`saucectl`}</inlineCode>{` in order to use an existing Sauce Connect tunnel with your test session:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`saucectl run --tunnel-id <tunnel-id>
`}</code></pre>
    <blockquote>
      <p parentName="blockquote">{`For more information on how to use the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--tunnel-id`}</inlineCode>{` flag, please visit the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
          "href": "/testrunner-toolkit/saucectl#tunnel-id"
        }}>{`CLI Reference`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    </blockquote>
    <p>{`To enable Sauce Connect Proxy in the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`config.yml`}</inlineCode>{`, use the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`tunnel`}</inlineCode>{` field:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-yaml",
        "metastring": "{3,4}",
        "{3,4}": true
      }}>{`sauce:
  concurrency: 3
  tunnel:
    id: sauce-ci-tunnel
  region: us-west-1
`}</code></pre>
    <blockquote>
      <p parentName="blockquote">{`For more information regarding how to install, setup, and configure Sauce Connect Proxy, please visit the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
          "href": "/secure-connections/sauce-connect"
        }}>{`Sauce Connect Proxy documentation`}</a></p>
    </blockquote>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "analyze-test-results-in-sauce-labs"
    }}>{`Analyze Test Results in Sauce Labs`}</h3>
    <p>{`After tests complete, Testrunner Toolkit uploads the test assets (logs, test results, and test videos) to your `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://app.saucelabs.com"
      }}>{`Sauce Labs account`}</a>{` and displays a job link like so:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-html"
      }}>{`https://app.saucelabs.com/tests/<job-number>
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`From this job link you can review, share, and analyze the test results just as you would with any other test framework executed on Sauce Labs.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "quick-demo"
    }}>{`Quick demo`}</h3>
    <img src={useBaseUrl('img/stt/saucectl-demo.gif')} alt="saucectl Demo" />
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "automation-framework-examples"
    }}>{`Automation Framework Examples`}</h2>
    <p>{`The examples here show how Pipeline testing can be used. Try them and find your own use cases. `}</p>
    <p>{`Every `}<strong parentName="p">{`Testrunner`}</strong>{` image comes with a preconfigured setup that allows you to focus on writing tests instead of tweaking with the configurations. Our initial `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`testrunner`}</inlineCode>{` flavors come either with Cypress, Playwright, or TestCafe as an automation framework. `}</p>
    <p>{`Below are example snippets in the following frameworks: `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress"
      }}>{`Cypress`}</a>{`, `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://playwright.dev/#version=v1.0.1&path=docs%2Fcore-concepts.md&q=browser"
      }}>{`Playwright`}</a>{`, and `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/documentation/reference/test-api/testcontroller/browser.html"
      }}>{`TestCafe`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <Tabs defaultValue="cypress" values={[{
      label: 'Cypress',
      value: 'cypress'
    }, {
      label: 'Playwright',
      value: 'playwright'
    }, {
      label: 'TestCafe',
      value: 'testcafe'
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="cypress" mdxType="TabItem">
        {
          /*https://github.com/saucelabs/saucectl/blob/master/tests/e2e/cypress/integration/example.test.js*/
        }
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-js"
          }}>{`context('Actions', () => {
        beforeEach(() => {
            cy.visit('https://example.cypress.io/commands/actions')
        })
        it('.type() - type into a DOM element', () => {
            // https://on.cypress.io/type
            cy.get('.action-email')
                .type('fake@email.com').should('have.value', 'fake@email.com')
        })
    })
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="playwright" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The Playwright testrunner image also exposes a global `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`browser`}</inlineCode>{` variable that represents Playwright's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "https://playwright.dev/#version=v1.0.2&path=docs%2Fcore-concepts.md&q=browser"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`Browser class`}</inlineCode></a>{`. In addition to that you also have access to a pre-generated `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "https://playwright.dev/#version=v1.0.2&path=docs%2Fcore-concepts.md&q=browser-contexts"
          }}>{`browser context`}</a>{` via `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`context`}</inlineCode>{` as well as to a `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "https://playwright.dev/#version=v1.0.2&path=docs%2Fcore-concepts.md&q=pages-and-frames"
          }}>{`page frame`}</a>{` via `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`page`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
        {
          /*https://github.com/saucelabs/saucectl/blob/master/tests/e2e/playwright/example.test.js
          */
        }
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-js"
          }}>{`describe('saucectl demo test', () => {
    test('should verify title of the page', async () => {
        await page.goto('https://www.saucedemo.com/');
        expect(await page.title()).toBe('Swag Labs');
    });
});
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="testcafe" mdxType="TabItem">
        {
          /*https://github.com/saucelabs/saucectl/blob/master/tests/e2e/testcafe/example.test.js
          */
        }
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-js"
          }}>{`import { Selector } from 'testcafe';
fixture \`Getting Started\`
    .page \`http://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/example\`

const testName = 'testcafe test'
test(testName, async t => {
    await t
        .typeText('#developer-name', 'devx')
        .click('#submit-button')
        .expect(Selector('#article-header').innerText).eql('Thank you, devx!');
});
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

;
